<p><b>The warning verse</b> (<a href="/wiki/Arabic" title="Arabic" class="mw-redirect">Arabic</a>:آیه الانذار ) is verse 214 of <a href="/wiki/Ash-Shu%27ara" title="Ash-Shu'ara">Ash-Shu'ara</a> chapter that was descended to <a href="/wiki/Muhammad" title="Muhammad">Muhammad</a>, <a href="/wiki/Prophet" title="Prophet">prophet and messenger</a> of <a href="/wiki/Allah" title="Allah">Allah</a>, in the third year of prophetic mission. According to this verse, prophet was appointed to warn his closest kindred for converting to <a href="/wiki/Islam" title="Islam">Islam</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-Kaya2015_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kaya2015-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<p></p>
